nib.text:
A woman was killed and three people were injured after a vehicle drove into protesters Uptown late Sunday night, police said. The driver is in police custody.

At 11:39 p.m., Minneapolis Police said, a vehicle drove into protesters on Lake Street and Girard Avenue.

A woman was transported to a hospital by EMS in critical condition. She was later pronounced dead.

At least two other protesters were treated at area hospitals for non-life-threatening injuries.

Police said that the protesters pulled the suspect from his car after the crash. He was taken into police custody and was being treated at an area hospital for unknown injuries.

Police said the suspects motive is not known.

CNN [reported](https://www.cnn.com/2021/06/14/us/minneapolis-protester-killed/index.html) that the group was protesting the killing of Winston Smith on June 3 by officers on a U.S. Marshals task force during an arrest attempt.

According to a [report](https://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/national-international/1-dead-vehicle-drives-into-minneapolis-protesters/3104948/) citing police, drugs or alcohol may have been a factor in the crash.
